PERSONAL MEDIA SERVER

Root location hosts Linktree. This frontpage will display a list of personal links. Similar to services like linktr.ee
In addition, location /speedtest hosts a OpenSpeedTest container. This is a great way to test connection speeds from remote locations to your home server.

watch. subdomain hosts Jellyfin. The perfect media server webapp. Serve all your movies through the web.

listen. subdomain hosts Navidrome. Self-hosted music streaming weebapp. Listen to your music with a UX like spotify.

drive. subdomain hosts Cloudreve. Chosen for its lightweight build compared to alternatives.
There are two other options which I commented out in the config files.
Most popular is NextCloud. This might be the most feature rich storage app out there.
Bewcloud is also a good alternative. Lightweight and easy set up.


DEPLOYING SERVER:

After downloading, edit nginx.conf
Change "domainname" to your host's domain

You must also edit the docker-compose.yaml to fit your configuration.
Change "domainname" to your host's domain
Change path bindings to desired storage locations for storage.

After completing previous steps, server is ready for deployment.

Run the following command:

	 docker compose up -d

After changes, you may add the following flags

--force-recreate: forces a new container to be created regardless of existing
--remove-orphans: prunes containers removed from compose

